## Lazy detail — the `.claude/rules/` pattern [pattern]

> The lever that keeps this file small. Any bulky, rarely-needed reference —
> path/alias maps, a checkpoint-clause menu, language-specific rules — lives in a
> file under `.claude/rules/`, and CLAUDE.md carries only a one-line *trigger* that
> tells Claude when to read it. Two ways `.claude/rules/` files load:
>
> - **Auto-loaded** — a file with `paths:` frontmatter (e.g. `**/*.py`) loads only
>   when you touch a matching file. Good for language/domain rules.
> - **Read-on-demand** — a file with no frontmatter loads only when a trigger in
>   CLAUDE.md tells Claude to read it. Good for lookup tables. Example trigger:

<!-- example: a read-on-demand pointer

## Paths

Before writing to any aliased repo/project location — or when a path isn't
obvious — read `.claude/rules/paths.md` first (it holds the alias→location map).

-->
